ce:section.ce:para:
Fig. 1
 shows the FTIR spectra of citric acid (CA), ethylenediamine (EDA), N-isopropylacrylamide (NIPAAM) and NIPAAM@C-Dots (123E-160-5h) prepared by hydrothermal reaction. Citric acid has a peak of CO stretching at 1721 cm−1. Additional peaks located in the range of 1260–1150 cm−1 can be assigned to the coupled C(OH) stretching and COH bending modes. The characteristic peaks of the NIPAAm at 1415 cm−1 (CH2
) and 1622 cm−1 (CC) were not detectable in the FTIR spectrum of NIPAAM@C-Dots. PNIPAAm showed a broad peak between 3200 and 3600 cm−1 due to NH bond stretching. FTIR spectrum of NIPAAM@C-Dots has characteristic peaks at 1638 cm−1 (NH), 1542 cm−1 (amide II), 1459 cm−1 (CH), 1267 cm−1 (CN).
